    "Ruckman, Dr. Peter S_": "The Delphic priests had bay leaves in their mouths when they prophesied.\n8. As to the exact time that this pre-Advent appearance takes place (typified by Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]`\u2019s conversion and the Lord\u2019s appearances to Ezekiel and Daniel), no one knows for sure\u2014at least not now. No faculty member of ANY major \u201crecognized\u201d school in America would ever find it out if the Lord gave them another hundred years, because their primary interest is not the Holy Bible: it is image, enrollment, reputation, and income ($$$). At one time, all the gravestones faced EAST (vs. 1). There is one judgment in heaven (the Judgment Seat of Christ) and another [v_Mat_25_19] one on earth (Matt. 25:19), but the nation of Israel is judged on earth in the Tribulation. His judgment, as an nation is OVER in Matthew\n8. Avoid injury and death. If you can do any of these things, it is God who enables you to do them. The sending from heaven (see",
